column5: Had to pay $55 a case last year. Can buy it cheaper on my own but then it gets weighed. What did anyone else pay for a case from an outfitter

In the past usually $45 to $55 which was acceptable. This year they want $75 per case since we are are doing a double flight out of Red Lake and using a comercial airline for the first 150+ miles. So it looks like we are going to invite a few old friends to join us, Jack Daniels and Jim Beam.
dont forget Johnie Walker, and Ron Rico as they may feel left out. 75$ a case..he just lost his right to "live the High Life".check minnow prices before buying as well.. jig gone
My 3 best friends. Johnnie Walker, Jack Daniels, Jim Beam. Now there's a country song waiting to be written! Joe
Already written. George Thorogood (sp) I Drink Alone
BeerMan, Where are you headed & where does the beer start & end up to =$75/case? Can it be pre-flighted?
$75 a case? Sheesh, I'd change outfitters. Last year we paid $37 and this year $40. Still half of what you'd pay in a tavern to drink.
